Local media is reporting the 16 minute, 50-second video by Nusrat al-Islam was released on telegram late last night. JOHANNESBURG Al-Qaeda s Mali branch has released a proof-of-life video of six foreign hostages, which reportedly includes South African Stephen McGowan.Local media is reporting the 16 minute, 50-second video by Nusrat al-Islam was released on telegram late last night.McGowan was abducted by al-Qaeda militants in 2011 along with Swiss national Johan Gustafson.The Swede was released earlier this week raising concerns about McGowan s fate.Humanitarian NGO the Gift of the Givers has been working to bring the South African home.